title: Homotopy lifting
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

Let $$p\colon \tilde{X} \to X$$ be a covering map and $$H\colon Y \times I \to X$$ some homotopy of maps $$f_0,f_1\colon Y \to X$$. Given any lift $$\tilde{f}_0\colon Y \to \tilde{X}$$ of $$f_0,$$ there is a unique lift $$\tilde{H}\colon Y \times I \to \tilde{X}$$ of $$H$$ agreeing with $$\tilde{f}_0$$ on $$Y \times \{0\}.$$
